#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:4
msgid "Embargoed hardware issues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:7
msgid "Scope"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:9
msgid ""
"Hardware issues which result in security problems are a different category "
"of security bugs than pure software bugs which only affect the Linux kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:13
msgid ""
"Hardware issues like Meltdown, Spectre, L1TF etc. must be treated "
"differently because they usually affect all Operating Systems (\"OS\") and "
"therefore need coordination across different OS vendors, distributions, "
"silicon vendors, hardware integrators, and other parties. For some of the "
"issues, software mitigations can depend on microcode or firmware updates, "
"which need further coordination."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:23
msgid "Contact"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:25
msgid ""
"The Linux kernel hardware security team is separate from the regular Linux "
"kernel security team."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:28
msgid ""
"The team only handles developing fixes for embargoed hardware security "
"issues. Reports of pure software security bugs in the Linux kernel are not "
"handled by this team and the reporter will be guided to contact the regular "
"Linux kernel security team (:ref:`Documentation/admin-guide/ "
"<securitybugs>`) instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:34
msgid ""
"The team can be contacted by email at <hardware-security@kernel.org>. This "
"is a private list of security officers who will help you coordinate a fix "
"according to our documented process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:38
msgid ""
"The list is encrypted and email to the list can be sent by either PGP or S/"
"MIME encrypted and must be signed with the reporter's PGP key or S/MIME "
"certificate. The list's PGP key and S/MIME certificate are available from "
"the following URLs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:43
msgid "PGP: https://www.kernel.org/static/files/hardware-security.asc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:44
msgid "S/MIME: https://www.kernel.org/static/files/hardware-security.crt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:46
msgid ""
"While hardware security issues are often handled by the affected silicon "
"vendor, we welcome contact from researchers or individuals who have "
"identified a potential hardware flaw."
msgstr ""

