#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:320
msgid "Encrypted mailing-lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:322
msgid ""
"We use encrypted mailing lists for communication. The operating principle of "
"these lists is that email sent to the list is encrypted either with the "
"list's PGP key or with the list's S/MIME certificate. The mailing list "
"software decrypts the email and re-encrypts it individually for each "
"subscriber with the subscriber's PGP key or S/MIME certificate. Details "
"about the mailing list software and the setup that is used to ensure the "
"security of the lists and protection of the data can be found here: https://"
"korg.wiki.kernel.org/userdoc/remail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:332
msgid "List keys"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:334
msgid ""
"For initial contact see the :ref:`Contact` section above. For incident "
"specific mailing lists, the key and S/MIME certificate are conveyed to the "
"subscribers by email sent from the specific list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:339
msgid "Subscription to incident-specific lists"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:341
msgid ""
"Subscription to incident-specific lists is handled by the response teams. "
"Disclosed parties who want to participate in the communication send a list "
"of potential experts to the response team so the response team can validate "
"subscription requests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:346
msgid ""
"Each subscriber needs to send a subscription request to the response team by "
"email. The email must be signed with the subscriber's PGP key or S/MIME "
"certificate. If a PGP key is used, it must be available from a public key "
"server and is ideally connected to the Linux kernel's PGP web of trust. See "
"also: https://www.kernel.org/signature.html."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../process/embargoed-hardware-issues.rst:352
msgid ""
"The response team verifies that the subscriber request is valid and adds the "
"subscriber to the list. After subscription the subscriber will receive email "
"from the mailing-list which is signed either with the list's PGP key or the "
"list's S/MIME certificate. The subscriber's email client can extract the PGP "
"key or the S/MIME certificate from the signature so the subscriber can send "
"encrypted email to the list."
msgstr ""
